Vice President Biden released a statement expressing his condolences for the victims of the mass shooting in Orlando. He praised the heroic actions of the police, first responders, and bystanders who saved lives during the attack. Biden emphasized that prayers are not enough to prevent these senseless mass shootings, and called the targeting of LGBT Americans evil and abhorrent. He stated that the investigation is ongoing, and the government will continue to bring those who harm America to justice. Biden concluded by reminding the world of the unity and strength of the American people in the face of tragedy.